  "texts": [
    "This seems to suggest that when answering correctly, ChatGPT displayed confidence in its responses and was able to pinpoint a more exact logic amongst its training data.",
    "However, it faltered when answering incorrectly and other logic groups, such as having an incorrect answer with consistent logic (IC), saw increases.",
    "In emulating a test taker, ChatGPT may be demonstrating some understanding of the correct answer but fails to make an accurate guess.",
    "Using 60% as a passing threshold, Gilson et al.",
    "tested different question sets and found that ChatGPT was capable of answering Step 1 and Step 2 questions correctly at rates higher than this standard [3]."
  ],
